TYPE: spatial <point/line/polygon> layer (<human-friendly theme>)

DESCRIPTION:
<1–2 lines describing what the table represents in GIS terms>

GEOMETRY:
- Geometry column: <geom_col_name>
- Geometry type: <Point/LineString/Polygon or unknown>
- Notes: <rules: prefer ST_Area/ST_Length on geometry; do not use stored area/length attributes if any>

LABEL / DISPLAY FIELDS (for map labels):
- <best 1–3 text columns that can be used as labels>

COLUMNS:
- <col> (<normalized type>) — <short meaning>

KEYWORDS / SYNONYMS:
<comma-separated, include Turkish + English; include common GIS user terms, e.g., cadde/sokak/mahalle/park etc.>

COMMON GIS QUERIES:
- <3–6 bullet lines describing typical filters/operations, including ILIKE usage and spatial predicates when relevant>
- If the table is spatial: include at least one ST_Intersects example description.
- If polygon: include area sorting hint (ORDER BY ST_Area(poly) DESC).
- If line: include length sorting hint (ORDER BY ST_Length(poly) DESC).
- If point/line used with polygon boundary: mention ST_Intersects or ST_DWithin as appropriate.

EXAMPLE QUESTIONS THIS TABLE SHOULD ANSWER:
- <3 short natural-language example questions in Turkish>

INFERENCE RULES
- Determine geometry column:
  - Prefer column named "poly", "geom", "geometry", "wkb_geometry".
  - Or any column whose data type is USER-DEFINED (assume geometry) unless clearly not.
- Determine geometry type:
  - If table name suggests roads/streets (yol, sokak, cadde, bulvar) => line.
  - If suggests neighborhoods/areas/parks/parcels (mahalle, park, parsel, alan) => polygon.
  - If suggests POI (eczane, okul, cami, durak, nokta) => point.
  - Otherwise, set Geometry type: unknown.
- Pick label fields:
  - Prefer columns ending with "_adi" (name fields), then "adi", then other meaningful text columns (e.g., mahalle_adi, bolge_adi, adres).
- If there are date/text project fields (proje_tarihi, revizyon_tarihi etc.), describe them briefly but keep the chunk compact.
- If you see columns like "alan", "uzunluk", "length", "area": explicitly add a note to compute using geometry (ST_Area/ST_Length) rather than the attribute.

